'''Ír''' was an [[wikipedia:Irish people|Irish]] king, according to the early version of the [[legendarium]] associated with ''[[The Book of Lost Tales]]''.<ref name=Ire/>

== History ==
Ír was the father of [[Íring]], who was commissioned by an [[wikipedia:Anglo-Saxons|Anglo-Saxon]] king [[Watol]] to build a road through his lands, which he was able to do in seven years. However, Watol's sons, the [[Wætlingas]], resented Íring's arrogance, and wagered that they could build an even better road in only three years.

King Ír, who was allied with the [[Orcs]] of the island of [[Íwerin]] (i.e. [[wikipedia:Ireland|Ireland]]), however, sent "all kinds of secret evils" at his son's behest, in order to stop the Wætlingas from reaching their goal.<ref name=Ire>{{PE|15}}, "[[Early Runic Documents]]", ''ER1d: Fourth page'', p. 96</ref>

